  ID: Knight
  Name: Pedro, Spanish arquebusier
  Icon: {fileID: 1208347981, guid: b2407ce4cf73ad348aec15ba9990f7a1, type: 3}
  Description: 'He left Toledo as a gambler, convinced war would convert luck into
    profit. He never wrote to his mother because failure embarrassed him. When his
    matchlock burst in his grip, three fingers became red pulp stuck to the barrel.


    Treatment:
    Wrap a tourniquet at mid-forearm, wait for the limb to pale. Use the saw to remove
    the pulped material in one decisive stroke. Cautery seals what ligature cannot.
    He will never reload a firearm.'
